{{Quote|To be directed by Lucas meant working with a creator of pop mythology, the man who directed possibly the most influential film ever made and lodged the notion of the Force in the collective psyche. I had twelve lines in two scenes with two days to prepare. All I knew about ''Star Wars: Episode II'' and the character was contained in the pages of script I still clutched after the screen test. Confidentiality clauses would prevent me talking of plot points (I didn't know any), the character's relationship to the story (no idea), even the character's name.|Graeme Blundell|<ref name="Amazon">{{Amazon|url=The-Naked-Truth-Life-Parts/dp/0733622615|text=The Naked Truth: A Life in Parts|archivedate=20230724173420}}</ref>}}
'''Graeme Blundell''' (born [[August 7]], [[1940s|1945]]<ref name="Vader Look" />) played [[Ruwee Naberrie/Legends|Ruwee Naberrie]] in [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Attack of the Clones'']] and [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|''Revenge of the Sith'']], although his scenes from Episode II did not make the final cut of the film. Blundell also stood in for [[Oliver Ford Davies]] ([[Sio Bibble/Legends|Sio Bibble]]) vocally in the scene with [[Queen/Legends|Queen]] [[Jamillia/Legends|Jamillia]]. Davies could not be there because he was in [[Wikipedia:Tokyo|Tokyo]], [[Wikipedia:Japan|Japan]], for a play.<ref>{{SWArchive|url=episode-ii/release/video/f20030307/index.html|text=Naberrie Family Reunion}}</ref>

